  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains a subtle W-AR-05 weakener: the primary validation result omits a comparedAgainst link, while the narrative discusses a comparator dataset that was acquired under ventricular assist device (VAD) steady-flow bench conditions rather than the pulsatile CPB operating envelope, rendering the comparator methodologically inappropriate for the declared COU despite superficial overlap in pump geometry and flow rates.",
